And then there are a few of us allied health. There are two

00:00:35.220 --> 00:00:38.520
part time social workers, I'm one of them. There's a

00:00:39.340 --> 00:00:43.380
registered clinical counselor and there's also a full time outreach worker

00:00:43.420 --> 00:00:47.820
which has been a new addition to the clinic over the last year

00:00:48.160 --> 00:00:52.140
and that has been really, really helpful. Everyone has noticed at the clinic

00:00:52.140 --> 00:00:55.820
that more people are engaged, more people are coming to appointments.

00:00:56.100 --> 00:01:00.120
We have someone on the ground in the community maintaining those really

00:01:00.120 --> 00:01:06.760
important relationships. We do you know various forms of trauma, grief,

00:01:06.760 --> 00:01:11.700
counseling, substance use counseling. We specifically work with Richmond

00:01:11.700 --> 00:01:15.860
residents. We're harm reduction as well so we have a lot of harm

00:01:15.860 --> 00:01:20.520
reduction supplies. It's really client led and we try to meet people where

00:01:20.520 --> 00:01:24.940
they're at and let them lead their journey.

